  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "13. Ye call me Master—Teacher.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Lord—learning of Him in the one capacity, obeying Him in the other.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ye say well, for so I am—The conscious dignity with which this claim is made is remarkable, following immediately on His laying aside the towel of service. Yet what is this whole history but a succession of such astonishing contrast from first to last?",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
